  • All Classes Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicMap  
    BasicMapTest
    This class contains unit tests used to test both the methods of the abstract Map class and the concrete BasicMap class.
    HTMLGenerator
    The HTMLGenerator class is responsible for generating the HTML maps for each player.
    HTMLGeneratorTest
    Tester class for the HTMLGenerator class.
    InvalidMapSizeException
    Exception intended to be thrown whenever the map size is too small or too large, depending on a number of criteria.
    InvalidNumberOfPlayersException
    Exception intended to be thrown whenever an invalid number of players is passed.
    Launcher
    Launches a maze-game session, defines the runtime routine.
    MainGame
    The MainGame class is responsible for coordinating the main logic of the game, and the primary interface for user input and provision of output to the user.
    MainGameTest
    Tester class for the main game loop logic.
    Map  
    MapCreator
    The MapCreator class is used to create different types of Map objects.
    MapCreatorTest  
    MoveException
    Simple exception to handle when a character beyond {'u', 'd', 'l', r'} has been supplied to move().
    NullPositionException
    Simple exception to handle when a player's Position position has not been set.
    Player  
    PlayerStatus
    The PlayerStatus enum defines the different states/outcome that can happen as a result of the player moving to a specific tile.
    PlayerTest
    Tester class for the Player class.
    Position
    Simple convenience class to maintain (x,y)--coordinates (representative of indices).
    SetupOperationPrecedenceException
    Simple unchecked exception intended to be thrown when setup is carried out in an incorrect order, resulting in some unstable state of the system variables.
    TileType
    The TileType enum defines the different types of tiles used in different maps.
